                  and disposal of chemicals; a review by the people responsible for 
                  undergraduate instruction in safety issues of students, teaching,  
                  research laboratories, among others.
            </p>
            <p class="warning-content">
                  The team worked on the laboratories of Tecnológico de Monterrey
                   campus Chihuahua in the school of engineering which fall under
                  the biosafety level 2. Before starting our work in the lab, 
                  all team members had to pass different safety tests and receive 
                  training. Those tests included an introduction in the laboratory 
                  machinery (i.e. centrifuge, plate reader, gel chamber, autoclave), 
                  but also covered the use of chemicals (i.e. chloroform, phenol, 
                  staining reagents). At all times, a supervisor or instructor was 
                  present when work was conducted in the laboratory. 
