            <h1>
               Personal Protective Equipment
            </h1>
            <hr class="safety-main-hr">
            <p>
                Working in a laboratory comes with potential risks, so  we have to follow certain rules to ensure individual and collective safety. 
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="row safety">
            <div class="container col-md-10 safety-accordion" target="#sfty-acc1">
                <span class="safety-spoiler">▼</span> 
                Personal protection. 
            </div>
            <div class="container col-md-9 safety-panel" id="sfty-acc1">
                   <p> We should always wear a lab coat, nitrile gloves and masks in order to avoid contact with dropplets, aerosols and other contaminants resulting from experiments. We should also wear long pants that cover the ankles, close-toed shoes and long hair (chin-length or longer) should be tied back. 
                    </p>
                    <div class="row acc-images">
                        <img src="/img/portrait_placeolder.png" alt="img" class="safety-acc-img">
                        <img src="/img/portrait_placeolder.png" alt="img" class="safety-acc-img">
                        <img src="/img/portrait_placeolder.png" alt="img" class="safety-acc-img">
                        <img src="/img/portrait_placeolder.png" alt="img" class="safety-acc-img">
                    </div>
                     <p>
                         Our personal belongings must stay away from the lab when handling infectious materials to prevent any contamination.
                     </p>
                     <div class="row acc-images">
                            <img src="/img/portrait_placeolder.png" alt="img" class="safety-acc-img">
                     </div>
                     <p>
                            The personal protective equipment is removed when leaving the lab, as it should not be taken outside unless it's appropriately packed and sealed.

                        </p>
                        <div class="row acc-images">
                               <img src="/img/portrait_placeolder.png" alt="img" class="safety-acc-img">
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            We should always disinfect our hands with 70% ethanol, applying it before and after we've put on the gloves, as well as washing our hands when entering the lab and after leaving it.

                        </p>
                        <div class="row acc-images">
                               <img src="/img/portrait_placeolder.png" alt="img" class="safety-acc-img">
                        </div>
            </div>

            <div class="container col-md-10 safety-accordion" target="#sfty-acc2">
                <span class="safety-spoiler">▼</span> 
                Autoclaves. 
            </div>
            <div class="container col-md-9 safety-panel"    id="sfty-acc2">
                   <p> Our lab is equipped with 3 Autoclaves: Tuttnauer, All American pressure steam sterilizer 25x, 110v and Autoclave vertical AESA, CV3. The autoclave is a strong heated container using high pressures and temperatures for steam sterilization.
                    </p>
                <div class="row acc-images">
                    <img src="/img/portrait_placeolder.png" alt="img" class="safety-acc-img">
